    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">1. f. 1v-60v: [Text selections] -- 2 f. 61v: Muhr ism Allāh -- 3. f. 62r: Muhr Jaʻfar al-Ṣādiq -- 4. f. 62v: Lafẓat al-Jalāl -- 5. f. 63r: Ism al-Nabī -- 6. f. 63v: Rasm Abū Bakr al-Ṣadīq -- 7. f. 64r: Rasm ʻUmar al-Fārūq -- 8. f. 64v: Rasm ʻUthmān -- 9. f. 65r: Rasm ʻAlī -- 10. f. 65v: Rasm Ḥasan -- 11. f. 66r: Rasm Ḥusayn -- 12. f. 66v: Muhr nubūwat al-Nabī -- 13. f. 67r: Muhr nubūwat al-Rasūl -- 14. f. 67v: Rasm ʻayn ʻAlī -- 15. f. 68r: Gūl Muḥammadī -- 16. f. 68v: Rasm kalām Allāh -- 17. f. 69r: Khirqat Rasūl Allāh</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: Written in 9 long lines; border-ruled.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: All pages have gold, foliate marginal fill; textblock is border-ruled in a wide gold band with a repeating geometric pattern in black and a narrow, red outside rule. Illuminated headpiece in gold with red, blue, and green on first opening (f. 1v); all section titles are in white ink on a gold background outlined in a colored box. Polychrome floral medallions in the margins and gold, lobed circles with orange and blue dots mark verse endings. 16 pages of illuminations and illustrations (f. 61v-69r).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: Copied in 1158 A.H. (1771 or 1772 C.E.) by Muṣṭafá al-maʻrūf bi-Kūtāhī (f. 60r).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Binding: Bound in paper with large, gilded flower and frame; remnants of a red spine.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">A letter dated November 1, 1923 to Edwin Wolf from Cyrus Adler of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning describing the manuscript is laid in.</subfield>
    </datafield>
